originalText.text: Went there a few nights ago to inquire about leaving my car there for a few days until I got new plates as I have done before. I had my friend translate because the guy didn't understand what I was asking. He told my friend that it would be possible, just to speak to the mgr the next day. He also told my friend to tell me the mgr spoke fluent english so there should be no confusion, just come between 9-4. I arrive at 10am and what do you know...its the guy that allowed me to leave the car before. There's about 4 guys hanging in the office, the only things missing were beer and cigars. The mgr and I was speaking but could barely hear each other due to the side convos. The mgr asked them to quite down, now total silence I ask him again and he looks at 2 the dudes behind him one of the say something in spanish then he asked me.make model and yr. I tell him then the dude on the side says some again in spanish. Then he says no we can't do that. I asked why you did before and the guy last night said it would be OK & you seemed interested until I told you my car's business. He said Mami not today. It might be some shady ish going on there because again he seemed interested at first.
